<p>
What you&#39;ll do (Responsibilities):</p>
<p>
Learn how to develop existing and new mobile applications for Big Nerd Ranch and for our clients</p>
<p>
Learn how to author stories (use cases, technical and functional requirements), tests and code</p>
<p>
Learn how to contribute to and participate in development meetings (stand-ups, kick-offs, retrospectives) and design sessions with teams and clients</p>
<p>
Learn how to collaborate with team members, consultants, designers and clients to provide accurate estimations, timelines and risks associated with development</p>
<p>
Learn how to contribute to the open-source community through code, documentation, teaching and speaking</p>
<p>
Learn how to write blog posts and code-review your teammates</p>
<p>
What you already need to know or have experience doing (Requirements):</p>
<p>
Have shipped one or more reasonably sized OpenGL applications (desktop or mobile)<br />
Experience with OpenGL ES 2.0 or OpenGL 3.0<br />
Comfortable with GLSL shader programming and the programmable pipeline<br />
Understand how OpenGL fits into a GUI framework and how to integrate event handling and 3D picking with the platform<br />
Use of higher level scene graph libraries like SceneKit or OpenSceneGraph is a plus, as would experience with geometry shaders or OpenGL 4 feedback.</p>
<p>
The benefits we offer:</p>
<p>
Health, dental, vision, life insurance; 401k matching, short- and long- term disability</p>
